DIAGNOSIS. — Up to 
3 mm
long. Colour brown, posterior margin of tergites dark brownish, some smaller specimens with olive-greenish spots. Surface of tergites structured similar to an orange surface, glabrous. Anal shield well-rounded, glabrous. Apical antennomere with 18-29 sensory cones. Third joint of posterior telopods broad, with well-rounded tip. Posterior side with up to 7 sclerotized black teeth, 1 small non-sclerotized lobe and 3 sclerotized spines (
Fig. 20J, K
). Second joint with long and slim, curved process, basally with 1 large spine. One stridulation rib on male harp (
Fig. 20F
) and 2 or 3 on each side of female washboard. Anal shield with 2 locking carinae, first small, second more than 2. times longer than first (
Fig. 20B
). Operculum of vulva small, not protruding above coxa, apically with 2 well-rounded lobes protruding to same height. Interior plate of vulva protruding as high as operculum (
Fig. 21A, B
).

Body measurements: males (
3 specimens
): length up to 22.00 (largest broken), width of thoracic shield up to 18., height of thoracic shield up to 10.. Females (specimens): length up to 2.4, width up to 32.4, height up to 1..

Habitus: body massive and high (
Fig. 20A
). Tergites and anal shield without hair, but surface completely covered with irregular small pits, comparable to an orange surface.

